  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <mi>A</mi>
  </math>. In the absence or lack of the limiting factor, the per capita growth rate decreases at a rate
  
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <mi>m</mi>
  </math> (
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <mi>m</mi>
  </math> typically models the amount of the limiting factor required to sustain proliferation, for example the consumption of oxygen or nutrient) We can now
