</p>
<p class="indent">
  In particular, in the case of a free fall (
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <mi>N</mi>
    <mo class="MathClass-rel">=</mo>
    <mi>∞</mi>
  </math> or
  
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <mi>φ</mi>
    <mo class="MathClass-rel">=</mo>
    <mn>0</mn>
  </math>) with friction (
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <mi>f</mi>
    <mo class="MathClass-rel">&gt;</mo>
    <mn>0</mn>
  </math>),
  
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <mi>r</mi>
  </math> reaches a maximal value:
  
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <msup>
      <mrow>
        <mi>r</mi>
      </mrow>
