    <mo class="MathClass-bin">∕</mo>
    <mi>f</mi>
  </math>. In this case, the per capita growth rate is given by two intrinsic cellular properties, metabolism and friction. This limiting speed is analogous to the limiting speed of a body in free fall in a medium with non-null viscosity, which
  is also given by medium and body properties.
